The paper deals with complexity theory, specifically algebraic complexity, quantum computing, and communication complexity. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses tools from quantum information (cs.QI), information theory (cs.IT), and discrete structures (cs.DS) to prove its results. Finally, the paper discusses the log-rank conjecture, which is a topic in logic and set theory (cs.LO).
